<p>Hi there, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dante1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6604322); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6604322&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1594097049" alt="Dante1221" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6604322)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dante1221" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6604322); return false;">Dante1221</a></span>! I'm an author on this site as well as a member of Community Outreach. It is always a pleasure to be introduced to someone from around the world since I am from the USA myself. If you are interested in translating, send me a PM and I can help guide you to the necessary resources. In the meantime, allow me to recommend <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1142">this article</a>. The following are several tips with resources for writing and reading here on the wiki!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Here&nbsp;you&nbsp;go!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Hope&nbsp;this&nbsp;helps!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Before writing, be sure to familiarize yourself with the SCP style, the drafting process, and the community. Doing so will greatly increase your chances of success. Also, don’t be afraid to fail. Most people's first articles go through the wringer. Try to follow the writing guides and get your article reviewed first. Failure the first time is no reason to give up. Failure just shows you what you need to do to improve on the next attempt.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>If you wish to try your hand at writing, try out our <a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/">Sandbox</a> page. You can make yourself a page here to store all of your drafts and ideas. You will also want to check out the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/how-to-write-an-scp">How To Write An SCP</a> page if you wish to learn more about how to create an SCP article. Before creating an SCP article as a first-time author, you should run your idea by the reviewers on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming</a> forum. On this forum, you will need to acquire 2 <span style="color: #00c800">greenlights</span> from established authors before you can post a draft to the <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/forum/c-50864/help:drafts-critique">Drafts Critique</a> forum to refine your article.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>If you happen to find an article you that you really enjoy, you can try finding more content from the same author by looking them up on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/members-pages">Authors' Page</a> hub.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>We have a very large collection of wonderful articles here on the wiki. However, a natural drawback to such a collection is that it is difficult to curate content to a user’s personal taste. As it stands, there is no way to search for content by genre. With the help of various community members, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/user-curated-lists">User-Curated Lists</a> was created to facilitate personal playlists of some amazing content to our users!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This should be plenty to get you well on your way! Let me know if this message was helpful at all, and if there's anything important you think I may have missed. Feel free to message me or others on the Community Outreach team if you have any questions. Good luck with your writing!</p>

							</div>

								
					
